╦[Left]
With fond memories of
MARTIN COOK
His guitar is silent 
His fingers no longer work
Those days have slipped away
All the hours that he played
Just a man who played his guitar.

[Center]
WITH HAPPY MEMORIES
JOYCE AND GERALD (GUS) STEELS
OF LOUGHTON, ESSEX
WHO LOVED PADSTOW AND
REGARDED IT AS THEIR SECOND HOME

[RIGHT]
In loving memory of
JOHN and EILEEN PEARCE
from Epsom, Surrey
who spent so many happy times
in and around Padstow"Ô
▀BARRY JOHN COTTON - 1937 - 1998
"A GENTLE GUEST. A WILLING HOST
AFFECTION DEEPLY PLANTED - 
IT'S STRANGE THAT THOSE WE MISS THE MOST
ARE THOSE WE TAKE FOR GRANTED"
- BETJEMAN'S CORNWALL
